      Uploads and processes a CSV file containing GTNet security import positions. Skips duplicates (same ISIN + currency within the same head).

      idGtNetSecurityImpHead - the header ID to associate positions with
      uploadFiles - array of uploaded CSV files (only first file is processed)

      Returns:

      Throws:
      Exception - if file processing fails

    • deleteLinkedSecurity

      GTNetSecurityImpPos deleteLinkedSecurity(Integer idGtNetSecurityImpPos, Integer idTenant)
      Deletes the linked security from a position and removes it from the system. The position itself remains and can be queried again via GTNet.

      This operation:

      1. Unlinks the security from the position (sets security reference to null)
      2. Deletes all history quotes for the security
      3. Deletes the security entity from the database
      Parameters:
      idGtNetSecurityImpPos - the position ID
      idTenant - the tenant ID for access verification
      Returns:
      the updated position with security set to null
      Throws:
      SecurityException - if tenant doesn't have access or position has no linked security

    • createFromImportTransactionHead

      GTNetSecurityImpHead createFromImportTransactionHead(Integer idTransactionHead, Integer idGtNetSecurityImpHead, String headName, Integer idTenant)
      Creates GTNet security import positions from an import transaction head. Reads ImportTransactionPos entries where security is null and (isin or symbolImp exists), then creates corresponding GTNetSecurityImpPos entries. Can create a new header or add to an existing one. Skips duplicates (same ISIN + currency) and entries with invalid data.
      Parameters:
      idTransactionHead - the import transaction head ID to read positions from
      idGtNetSecurityImpHead - optional existing header ID to add positions to (null to create new)
      headName - name for new header (required if idGtNetSecurityImpHead is null)
      idTenant - the tenant ID for access verification
      Returns:
      the GTNet security import header (existing or newly created)
      Throws:
      SecurityException - if tenant doesn't have access to the import transaction head
